; A bitwise op (iand/ior/ixor/ishl/ishr/…) applied to floats. The checker permits
; the shape, but codegen has no integer-bitwise LLVM op for a float type: Rust's
; src/codegen.rs EBin float arm returns `Err("codegen: bitwise op on a float")`,
; a spanless `error: <msg>` exit 1. The self-host used to SIGABRT with UNIMPLEMENTED.
(defn main [] (-> :i64) (do (iand 1.0 2.0) 0))
